The story of the media man accused of grooming and sexually molesting schoolboys over years is nothing short of a crime thriller. At the height of the campaign, sixteen days of activism against abuse, it strengthens the perception in society of an abuser who does not fit the mould: he did not look it, he did not act it, it’s impossible that he did it … Yet we expect women to walk away. What does an abuser have to look like for a victim to not have to jump through the fires of hell to be believed? Were the exposes...